Pastor Enoch Adeboye of the Redeemed Christian Church of God, RCCG, on Sunday declared that Coronavirus will soon be over in Africa. Adeboye said COVID-19 will soon decline in Nigeria and Africa. Speaking during a live service, the clergyman cautioned Nigerians against traveling out for two months. He said: “Coronavirus will soon decline in Africa. I urge you to avoid traveling out of Nigeria for 2 months. “We have entered the declining stage for coronavirus, let’s endeavor to maintain hygiene and stay home.” Meanwhile, the toll of confirmed case of COVID-19 in the
country stands at 542. This followed 49 new cases confirmed by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC.